<script type="text/javascript">podPressShowHidePlayer('1', 'http://www.survivalpodcast.net/audio/2013/2-13/epi-01067-calls-2-8-13.mp3', 290, 24, 'false', 'http://www.thesurvivalpodcast.com/wp-content/plugins/podpress/images/vpreview_center.png', 'Episode-1067- Listener Calls for 2-8-13', 'The Survival Podcast');</script><div id="attachment_6212" style="width: 140px" class="wp-caption alignleft"><a href="http://www.thesurvivalpodcast.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/jackspirko.jpg"><img class=" wp-image-6212" title="jackspirko" alt="Join Me Today as I Answer Your eMails" src="http://www.thesurvivalpodcast.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/jackspirko.jpg" width="130" height="139" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Join Me Today as I Answer Your Calls</p></div>
<p>Today on The Survival Podcast I take your calls on cooking, <a target="_blank" title="silver" href="http://www.thesurvivalpodcast.com/episode-51-options-and-reasons-to-invest-in-silver">silver</a>, guns, <a title="permaculture" href="http://tspwiki.com/index.php?title=Permaculture">permaculture</a>, fedge&#8217;s, community, remote prepping, paddock shift, chickens, privacy issues, self defense and more .</p>
<p>Remember to be on a show like this one just pick up your phone and call <strong><span style="color: #800000;">866-65-THINK</span></strong>. The best way to improve your chances of being on the air is ask your question or make your point up front, then provide details.</p>
<p>Also please do your best to call from a quite area with a good connection and speak up so you can be well heard. I can’t put all calls on the air but I do my best to get most of them on.</p>
<p><strong><span style="color: #800000;">Join Me Today As I Respond to Your Calls and Discuss&#8230;</span></strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Preparing rice without using heat at all</li>
<li>Are there any concerns about exchangeability of different forms of silver</li>
<li>Is paleo eating sustainable long term as a way of life</li>
<li>Choosing between a carbine or a handgun</li>
<li>Another guru says PMs are bad and can&#8217;t back it up</li>
<li>Thoughts on varieties for a fedge &#8220;food hedge&#8221;</li>
<li>The importance of friends and community in a breakdown</li>
<li>Thoughts on overwintering chickens</li>
<li>Paddock shift for reasons other then ground disturbance/grazing</li>
<li>A real story about sharing shooting with others</li>
<li>Prepping when you are already in a remote area (like an island)</li>
<li>Self defense at home when a <a target="_blank" title="gun" href="http://tspwiki.com/index.php?title=Firearm">gun</a> is not an option</li>
<li>Concerns about the government knowing about your silver</li>
<li>Thoughts on the non concern about small flock chicken coop odor</li>
<li>Who should be trusted and is bigotry one way</li>
</ul>
<p><strong><span style="color: #800000;">Resources for today’s show…</span></strong></p>
<ul>
