		<div class="comment-body"><p>You know what I never thought about it but that is another benefit.  In the past I would get bad rashes in the heat.  I would get them on my back and sides, just red, and little itchy bumps like a very mild case of poison ivy.  I know it was heat that brought it out because they would vanish in a cool shower and I never got this in winter.  I would also really break out in the heat around where I shave my neck.  I would even get some acne in the hottest months.  Not the occasional pimple we all get from time to time I mean like I was back in high school every August.  </p>
<p>I never really even thought about this until you brought it up.  All of this is in my past, I haven&#8217;t experienced any of it in over two year.  I have to agree there is a connection in getting off toxic foods and this type of thing.</p>
