		<div class="comment-body"><p>No-heat rice: I&#8217;ll try the &#8220;no heat&#8221; method but imagine it may only work with &#8220;Minute Rice&#8221; varieties unless you soak it for a very long time. A very fuel efficient alternative is thermos cooking. It&#8217;s good for rice and quinoa (my favorite). It still takes a few hours but you save fuel because you don&#8217;t need simmering. Just use some extra hot water when making your morning coffee, a good thermos, and you&#8217;ll have quinoa or rice ready for lunch or supper.<br />
<a href="http://blog.trailcooking.com/2012/08/08/the-thermos-method-for-quinoa/" rel="nofollow">http://blog.trailcooking.com/2012/08/08/the-thermos-method-for-quinoa/</a></p>
