<p>You also can&#8217;t say your boys will not be around gays, likely 10% of society you walk by every day is gay.  Likely they will have a friend or two in their youth that will end up being gay.</p>
<p>The problem is there shouldn&#8217;t even be a need for terms like gay rights or woman&#8217;s rights or minority rights.  We are all humans, done, the end.  Flat out I have unlearned my taught hatred of people due to race and sexual choice.  It was quite ingrained in my family.  When I made a black friend in High School many of my family were &#8220;ashamed&#8221;, yes ashamed that I would be friends with a black person.  I am glad I got that figured out before going into the military.  </p>
<p>So you go around thinking you can &#8220;fix&#8221; gay people with science or more accurately science fiction.  Go around thinking God hates gays and sends them to hell or whatever, that is your choice but let me tell you teaching children this won&#8217;t force your fear into their hearts.  In the end they will choose for themselves how to treat others.  Sometimes the harder a parent pushes a child to be against something the more it tends to back fire.  I am proof of that.</p>
<p>See I don&#8217;t want to go hanging around with a bunch of gay men or women for that matter in my day to day life.  Like most people I like to hang with people that are like me.  People that want to discuss guns, hunting, fishing and out door stuff.  I like my guy friends to have women who get along with my wife so we can all do stuff together.  But that doesn&#8217;t require me to treat a person differently if they happen to be gay, there are plenty of people I meet who are not gay that I also don&#8217;t really want to be hanging around day to day and many for no actual negative reasons, they just don&#8217;t have a lot in common with me.</p>
<p>Just do this for me dude as long as you are going to have this in your heart and soul, if ever the day comes you need a organ or blood transfusion to stay alive, ask if it is from strait people before you take it.  I mean you wouldn&#8217;t want to go walking around with a gay kidney or liver or worse a gay heart right?</p>
</div>

